From f00bc66c395f2c601c17376b9b64970fba675116 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 10:05:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] process: bound fork-child checkin wait with a timeout

waitForChildAfterFork() blocked forever on the fork-wait semaphore, so a
child that never checked in wedged the parent's microthread permanently.
Add dtape_semaphore_down_timeout (+ dtape_semaphore_wait_result_timed_out)
and wait at most 30s; waitForChildAfterFork() now returns bool and
ForkWaitForChild replies -ETIMEDOUT on timeout. Add fork-child checkin
lifecycle logging.
